main event: A ground-radar observation of a silver, oval-shaped, fast-moving unidentified flying object was reported in Central New Jersey in August 1958.
interesting points: The UFO was described as traveling at a velocity of 1200 mph and at an altitude of approximately 3000 ft.
It traveled from east to west and the observation lasted for 5 minutes.
Witnesses reported seeing the object traveling at a fantastic speed, with a curvature of the earth-uphill and downhill.
The object appeared to oscillate back and forth and exhibited a dim light source behind the craft.
The report includes hand-drawn sketches of possible shapes of UFOs from the years 1943, 1951, and 1953.
sighted object: silver, oval-shaped, fast-moving unidentified flying object
